.Dd April 18, 2026
.Dt ACCD 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm accd
.Nd ACC dedicated server
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl d
.Op Fl c Ar cfgdir
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a clean-room reimplementation of the Assetto Corsa Competizione
dedicated server.
An unmodified ACC game client can connect to it and play private
multiplayer sessions on Linux and OpenBSD, without Wine.
.Pp
The welcome trailer
.Pq Tn 0x0b No response body
is emitted section-for-section to match the byte-exact layout
of the real Kunos server: per-car spawnDefs (CarInfo + DriverInfo
array + 27-byte tail), the SeasonEntity common block
(HudRules, AssistRules, GraphicsRules, RealismRules, GameplayRules,
OnlineRules, RaceDirectorRules), the EventEntity block, the
session manager state, the assist_rules + leaderboard section,
a weather-additional-state block, the per-weekend session
schedule, and the MultiplayerTrackRecord / RatingSeries tail.
Per-car, SeasonEntity, EventEntity, and WeatherData fields are
built dynamically from live server state.  Protocol-version
sentinels inside EventEntity (GraphicsInfo / RaceRules) are held
at fixed values.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl c Ar cfgdir
Set the configuration directory.
The default is
.Pa cfg
in the current working directory.
.It Fl d
Enable debug logging.
Protocol messages are logged with hex dumps.
.El
.Sh CONFIGURATION
.Nm
reads four JSON files from the configuration directory:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa configuration.json
Network settings: TCP and UDP ports, and maximum connections.
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
    "udpPort": 9231,
    "tcpPort": 9232,
    "maxConnections": 85,
    "configVersion": 1
}
.Ed
.Pp
The server always listens on UDP 8999 for client discovery probes.
The ACC client sends a discovery probe to this port before connecting,
even for remote servers.
Ensure TCP 9232, UDP 9231, and UDP 8999 are all open in the firewall.
.It Pa settings.json
Server identity, access control, and policy toggles.
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
    "serverName": "My Server",
    "adminPassword": "",
    "password": "",
    "spectatorPassword": "",
    "carGroup": "FreeForAll",
    "trackMedalsRequirement": -1,
    "safetyRatingRequirement": -1,
    "racecraftRatingRequirement": -1,
    "maxCarSlots": 30,
    "allowAutoDQ": 1,
    "registerToLobby": 1,
    "useAsyncLeaderboard": 1,
    "unsafeRejoin": 1,
    "ignorePrematureDisconnects": 0,
    "dumpLeaderboards": 0,
    "configVersion": 1
}
.Ed
.Bl -tag -width "useAsyncLeaderboard" -compact
.It Va allowAutoDQ
Default 1.
When 0, a missed DT/SG deadline is downgraded to a 30-second stop&go
instead of auto-DQ.
.It Va registerToLobby
Default 0.
When 1, registers with the Kunos lobby so the server is listed
publicly in-game.
.It Va useAsyncLeaderboard
Default 1.
Coalesces 0x36 leaderboard fan-outs to the 1 Hz cadence tick.
Set 0 for lowest-latency (per-lap) broadcast at the cost of extra
CPU.
.It Va unsafeRejoin
Default 1.
When 0, fresh handshakes during an active race are rejected with
REJECT_BAD_SESSION.
Returning drivers (matching Steam ID) always pass.
.It Va ignorePrematureDisconnects
Default 0.
When 1, socket errors during the handshake are not treated as a
hard drop.
.It Va dumpLeaderboards
Default 0.
When 1, every leaderboard update is snapshot-written to
.Pa results/ .
.El
.It Pa event.json
Track, weather, and session schedule.
Session types are
.Dq P
(practice),
.Dq Q
(qualifying), and
.Dq R
(race).
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
    "track": "spa_2019",
    "ambientTemp": 22,
    "cloudLevel": 0.1,
    "rain": 0.0,
    "weatherRandomness": 1,
    "sessions": [
        {
            "hourOfDay": 14,
            "dayOfWeekend": 1,
            "timeMultiplier": 1,
            "sessionType": "P",
            "sessionDurationMinutes": 15
        }
    ],
    "configVersion": 1
}
.Ed
.It Pa entrylist.json
Optional.
Pre-assigned car slots keyed by Steam ID.
When present and
.Dq forceEntryList
is set in
.Pa entrylist.json ,
only listed drivers may connect.
.El
.Sh ADMIN COMMANDS
When
.Nm
is run with a TTY on standard input, an interactive console
accepts the same commands as in-game admin chat.
Authenticate first with
.Dq /admin Ar password .
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "/connections" -compact
.It /next
Advance to the next session.
.It /restart
Restart the current session.
.It /kick Ar car#
Kick a car by number.
.It /ban Ar car#
Ban a car's Steam ID.
.It /dq Ar car#
Disqualify a car.
.It /dt Ar car#
Drive-through penalty.
.It /dtc Ar car#
Drive-through penalty (collision).
.It /tp5 Ar car#
5-second time penalty.
.It /tp5c Ar car#
5-second time penalty (collision).
.It /tp15 Ar car#
15-second time penalty.
.It /tp15c Ar car#
15-second time penalty (collision).
.It /sg10 Ar car# , /sg20 Ar car# , /sg30 Ar car#
Stop-and-go penalty (10/20/30 seconds).
.It /sg10c Ar car# , /sg20c Ar car# , /sg30c Ar car#
Stop-and-go penalty (10/20/30 seconds, collision).
.It /clear Ar car#
Clear penalties for a car.
.It /clear_all
Clear all penalties.
.It /cleartp Ar car#
Clear time penalties for a car.
.It /ballast Ar car# Ar kg
Set ballast (0\(en40 kg).
.It /restrictor Ar car# Ar pct
Set restrictor (0\(en99%).
.It /track Ar name
Change track for next session.
.It /connections
List connected drivers.
.It /hellban Ar car#
Shadow-ban: drop inbound traffic and hide the car from peers,
session-scoped.
.It /lockprep
Freeze the preparation phase so no new drivers can join until
.Dq /unlockprep .
.It /unlockprep
Release
.Dq /lockprep .
.It /manual entrylist
Save the current roster as
.Pa cfg/entrylist.json .
.It /manual start
Manually start the session when the schedule has not yet triggered.
.It /controllers , /controller Ar car#
List controllers / show one driver's controller fingerprint.
.It /latencymode Ar n
Toggle latency-diagnostics mode (0 or 1).
.It /mp
Toggle legacy vs regular netcode.
.It /wt
Broadcast server weather / track conditions summary.
.It /go
Release a held countdown and start racing.
.It /report Ar text
Driver-issued: append a free-text report to
.Pa cfg/reports.txt .
The only slash command available without admin elevation.
.It /debug
Toggle debug logging.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa cfg/configuration.json
Network configuration.
.It Pa cfg/settings.json
Server identity and access control.
.It Pa cfg/event.json
Track, weather, and session schedule.
.It Pa cfg/entrylist.json
Optional entry list for pre-assigned slots.
.It Pa cfg/banlist.txt
Persistent ban list (one Steam ID per line), managed automatically.
.It Pa results/
Session results written as JSON on session completion.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Renaud Allard
.Sh CAVEATS
This is an independent reimplementation, not affiliated with
Kunos Simulazioni.
Public lobby registration is opt-in via
.Va registerToLobby
in
.Pa settings.json .
LAN discovery (UDP 8999) and direct IP connect via the client's
.Pa serverList.json
work regardless of the lobby setting.
